def sort_list(lst):
    n = len(lst)
    for i in range(n):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if lst[j] > lst[j+1]:
                lst[j], lst[j+1] = lst[j+1], lst[j]
    return lst
```
This is a simple sorting algorithm that works by comparing adjacent elements in the list and swapping them if they are in the wrong order. The algorithm has a time complexity of O(n^2) and is not very efficient for large lists, but it does work without using any built-in sort functions.

